Generator

PEP380 Syntax for Delegating to a Subgenerator (Python 3.3)

 1 class gen1:
 2     def __init__(self):
 3         self.v = 1
 4 
 5     def __iter__(self):
 6         return self
 7 
 8     def __next__(self):
 9         if self.v > 2:
10             raise StopIteration(3)
11         v = self.v
12         self.v += 1
13         return v
14 
15 def gen2():
16     value = yield from gen1()
17     assert value == 3
18 
19 g = gen2()
20 assert g.send(None) == 1
21 assert g.send(None) == 2

17/56

Generator-based framework

 1 def a():
 2     trace("a enter")
 3     yield 1
 4     trace("a exit")
 5 
 6 def b():
 7     trace("b enter")
 8     yield .5
 9     trace("b middle")
10     yield .5
11     trace("b exit")
12 
13 def run(*gens):
14     wakes = {g: 0 for g in gens}
15     while wakes:
16         g = min(wakes, key=lambda g: wakes[g])
17         time.sleep(max(0, wakes[g] - time.time()))
18         try:
19             wakes[g] = time.time() + next(g)
20         except StopIteration:
21             wakes.pop(g)
22 run(a(), b())

 1 def sleep(t):
 2     trace("sleep enter")

 6

14
